    "message_2": "To solve the given initial value problem using the fourth-order Runge-Kutta method, we will follow these steps:\n\n1. Define the function f(x, y) = 2x + y\n2. Set the initial conditions x0 = 0 and y0 = 1\n3. Set the step size h = 0.1\n4. Calculate the approximate value of y when x = 0.5 using the fourth-order Runge-Kutta method\n\nThe fourth-order Runge-Kutta method is given by the following formulas:\n\nk1 = h * f(x_n, y_n)\nk2 = h * f(x_n + h/2, y_n + k1/2)\nk3 = h * f(x_n + h/2, y_n + k2/2)\nk4 = h * f(x_n + h, y_n + k3)\n\ny_{n+1} = y_n + (k1 + 2*k2 + 2*k3 + k4) / 6\n\nNow, let's apply the method:\n\nStep 1: Define the function f(x, y)\nf(x, y) = 2x + y\n\nStep 2: Set the initial conditions\nx0 = 0\ny0 = 1\n\nStep 3: Set the step size\nh = 0.1\n\nStep 4: Calculate the approximate value of y when x = 0.5\n\nWe need to perform 5 iterations to reach x = 0.5 (since x0 = 0 and h = 0.1).\n\nIteration 1:\nk1 = 0.1 * f(0, 1) = 0.1 * (2*0 + 1) = 0.1\nk2 = 0.1 * f(0.05, 1.05) = 0.1 * (2*0.05 + 1.05) = 0.115\nk3 = 0.1 * f(0.05, 1.0575) = 0.1 * (2*0.05 + 1.0575) = 0.11575\nk4 = 0.1 * f(0.1, 1.115) = 0.1 * (2*0.1 + 1.115) = 0.1315\n\ny1 = 1 + (0.1 + 2*0.115 + 2*0.11575 + 0.1315) / 6 = 1.1105\n\nIteration 2:\nk1 = 0.1 * f(0.1, 1.1105) = 0.1 * (2*0.1 + 1.1105) = 0.13105\nk2 = 0.1 * f(0.15, 1.176025) = 0.1 * (2*0.15 + 1.176025) = 0.1476025\nk3 = 0.1 * f(0.15, 1.1833125) = 0.1 * (2*0.15 + 1.1833125) = 0.14833125\nk4 = 0.1 * f(0.2, 1.22125) = 0.1 * (2*0.2 + 1.22125) = 0.164225\n\ny2 = 1.1105 + (0.13105 + 2*0.1476025 + 2*0.14833125 + 0.164225) / 6 = 1.22175\n\nIteration 3:\nk1 = 0.1 * f(0.2, 1.22175) = 0.1 * (2*0.2 + 1.22175) = 0.164175\nk2 = 0.1 * f(0.25, 1.3038375) = 0.1 * (2*0.25 + 1.3038375) = 0.18038375\nk3 = 0.1 * f(0.25, 1.31175625) = 0.1 * (2*0.25 + 1.31175625) = 0.181175625\nk4 = 0.1 * f(0.3, 1.353) = 0.1 * (2*0.3 + 1.353) = 0.1973\n\ny3 = 1.22175 + (0.164175 + 2*0.18038375 + 2*0.181175625 + 0.1973) / 6 = 1.3535\n\nIteration 4:\nk1 = 0.1 * f(0.3, 1.3535) = 0.1 * (2*0.3 + 1.3535) = 0.19735\nk2 = 0.1 * f(0.35, 1.452175) = 0.1 * (2*0.35 + 1.452175) = 0.2135175\nk3 = 0.1 * f(0.35, 1.46089375) = 0.1 * (2*0.35 + 1.46089375) = 0.214089375\nk4 = 0.1 * f(0.4, 1.51425) = 0.1 * (2*0.4 + 1.51425) = 0.230425\n\ny4 = 1.3535 + (0.19735 + 2*0.2135175 + 2*0.214089375 + 0.230425) / 6 = 1.5145\n\nIteration 5:\nk1 = 0.1 * f(0.4, 1.5145) = 0.1 * (2*0.4 + 1.5145) = 0.23045\nk2 = 0.1 * f(0.45, 1.629725) = 0.1 * (2*0.45 + 1.629725) = 0.2469725\nk3 = 0.1 * f(0.45, 1.63894375) = 0.1 * (2*0.45 + 1.63894375) = 0.247894375\nk4 = 0.1 * f(0.5, 1.695) = 0.1 * (2*0.5 + 1.695) = 0.2645\n\ny5 = 1.5145 + (0.23045 + 2*0.2469725 + 2*0.247894375 + 0.2645) / 6 = 1.695\n\nSo, the approximate value of y when x = 0.5 is y5 = 1.695."
